<pdd-reason>Agentic checkup session runner for explicitly requested prompt review, interactive, and auto modes.</pdd-reason>
<pdd-interface>
{
  "type": "module",
  "module": {
    "classes": [
      {"name": "AgentEvent", "kind": "dataclass"},
      {"name": "CheckupSession", "kind": "class"},
      {"name": "TerminalCheckupSession", "kind": "class"},
      {"name": "RecordingCheckupSession", "kind": "class"},
      {"name": "CheckupAgent", "kind": "class"}
    ],
    "constants": [
      {"name": "MODE_REVIEW", "value": "review"},
      {"name": "MODE_INTERACTIVE", "value": "interactive"},
      {"name": "MODE_AUTO", "value": "auto"}
    ]
  }
}
</pdd-interface>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_interactive_main_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_planner_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_report_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_tools_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_prompt_main_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Goal
Write `pdd/checkup_agent.py`.

% Requirements
- Execute prompt checkup only when explicitly selected by CLI flags such as `--interactive`, `--auto`, or `--planner`.
- Support review, interactive, and auto modes without making bare `pdd checkup <prompt>` agentic by default.
- Terminal interactive mode MUST expose Option A, Option B, keep current / skip, custom fix, rationale/details, and question affordances.
- Low-risk repairs may be queued or applied when `--apply` is set; medium-risk repairs are saved for review; high-risk findings remain manual TODOs.
- When applying patches, use `checkup_interactive_main.apply_approved_patches` and respect non-zero applicator results.
- Emit truthful accounting and blocking decisions; never claim success when unresolved strict failures remain.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Opt-in agentic path
Bare `pdd checkup <prompt>` MUST NOT instantiate or run `CheckupAgent`.

R2 - Interactive UX options
Interactive terminal prompts MUST include Option A, Option B, keep current / skip, custom fix, and rationale/details affordances.

R3 - Risk gating
The agent MUST NOT auto-apply high-risk findings; medium-risk findings MUST be saved for review rather than applied automatically.
</contract_rules>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/checkup_agent.py`
